    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX 2150 - INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive pulley on the crankshaft. Tighten the crankshaft nut as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s04004_42.xml" xrefid="hl0400405">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace the discharge and inlet fittings ( if applicable) and tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s04004_42.xml" xrefid="hl0400405">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the governor, replace any supporting bracketry and mount the compressor in its
                operating position. If belt driven, reinstall the belt(s) and adjust to proper tension. See
                <hotlnk document="s04004_41.xml" xrefid="hl0400401">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect all air, cooling and lubrication lines. Start engine and inspect for leakage from
                the air, cooling and/or lubrication lines and connections.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recharge all the air reservoirs in the system to 100-125 psi (687-862 kPa).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
